I extract them from the fact that the emotional system, such as the fear system, is activated in the brain conscious of its own activity.
What we refer to as “fear” is the mental state in which we are located when the activity of the defense system located in the brain (or its consequences, such as bodily reactions) uses operational memory.
Viewed from this point of view, the feelings are closely related to those areas of the cortex, which are characterized by primates, and especially people.
